    C^n monoid #

    A C^n monoid is a monoid that is also a C^n manifold, in which multiplication is a C^n map of the product manifold G √ó G into G.

    In this file we define the basic structures to talk about C^n monoids: ContMDiffMul and its additive counterpart ContMDiffAdd. These structures are general enough to also talk about C^n semigroups.

    source
    class ContMDiffAdd {ùïú : Type u_1} [NontriviallyNormedField ùïú] {H : Type u_2} [TopologicalSpace H] {E : Type u_3} [NormedAddCommGroup E] [NormedSpace ùïú E] (I : ModelWithCorners ùïú E H) (n : WithTop ‚Ñï‚àû) (G : Type u_4) [Add G] [TopologicalSpace G] [ChartedSpace H G] extends IsManifold I n G :
    Prop

    Basic hypothesis to talk about a C^n (Lie) additive monoid or a C^n additive semigroup. A C^n additive monoid over G, for example, is obtained by requiring both the instances AddMonoid G and ContMDiffAdd I n G.

    • compatible {e e' : PartialHomeomorph G H} : e ‚àà atlas H G ‚Üí e' ‚àà atlas H G ‚Üí e.symm.trans e' ‚àà contDiffGroupoid n I
    • contMDiff_add : ContMDiff (I.prod I) I n fun (p : G √ó G) => p.1 + p.2
